  "text": "In the presence of three or more boundaries, each loop operator w(ℓ) can be expanded in non-negative powers of ℓ [CITATION_1] , or equivalently, W (µ B ) can be expanded in inverse powers of µ B [CITATION_2] . Each term in this expansion represents a local disturbance of the surface, and is thus equivalent to the insertion of a local operator.",
